                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-04-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear</hi> Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi>: Referring to
                    your letter of the 9th instant, in which you inquire, at the instance of the
                    Treasury Department, whether Her Majesty’s Government have issued an order in
                    council relating to the seal fisheries in Bering Sea for 1896, I have the honor
                    to state that I am not aware of any hew order in council having been issued or
                    being in contemplation.</p>
                <p>I presume that “The Bering Sea award orders in council 1894 and 1895” will
                    continue to regulate the fishery, as regards British sealing vessels.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
